node.person.name: Shaun Abrahamson
node.areas_of_interest_freeform: We know that climate is about more than carbon—it’s also about force multipliers like asset finance and distribution. We believe the best climate solutions don’t look like climate solutions at all, just better, faster, and cheaper products and services. We prefer rapid deployment that will get us close to 1.5C in warming while upgrading our systems to make them more resilient. But we’ll also look at moonshot opportunities because we know we need a plan B.

node.person.name: Charlie Pinto
node.areas_of_interest_freeform:
I am interested in ideas that build a better future for humanity. I am a sector-agnostic, thesis-driven, and market first investor primarily backing founders building the following:
(1) "Machine Learning first" companies that help workers achieve better outcomes (B2B, B2C)
(2) Biotech companies indirectly or directly curing disease.
(3) Platform companies accelerating innovation.

How I help founders: Installing culture, leadership, risk management, grand strategy, people management.

node.areas_of_interest_freeform: Once a trend or category is hot and well defined, it is typically an overcrowded place for angel investors to write checks, so I try to avoid investing in trends.  I tend to be most interested in founders with superior insight into their chosen market and the ability to attract quality management, investors and industry partners.

node.person.name: Yoann Berno
node.areas_of_interest_freeform:
After building and investing in top tech startups throughout his career, I co-founded Climentum Capital, a Climate Tech VC fund that focuses on investing in game-changing technological solutions to combat the worsening climate crisis.

My mission now is to democratize climate investing as a force multiplier to accelerate the climate transition with Climate Insiders.

node.person.name: Eric Rosenblum
node.areas_of_interest_freeform:
Seed-stage AI applications (for me *personally*; as a firm, we are far broader). 

As a firm, we have a fairly strong interest in highly technical founders (75% of our companies have at least 1 PhD founder) and founders who are able to seamlessly operate between the US and China (65% of our companies have at least 1 Chinese founder). Neither of these interests are "filters", though (ie., it is not required).

My global perspective helps me to identify markets opportunities. I seek frontier markets - both geographic markets and sectors that are poised for growth.

Focused on supporting early-stage companies at the forefront of our climate and environmental crisis, agnostic of the industry - we invest and support founders in energy, mobility, food/ag, heavy industry and the built environment. 

Support in all things growth - customer discovery / validation, sales, marketing, and fundraising.

node.person.name: Team Global
node.areas_of_interest_freeform:
We work across 5 themes: 
1) MOBILITY: Air taxis, air scooters, micro-mobility and electrification.

2) CLEAN ABUNDANT ENERGY: Energy storage and generation, including battery technologies and nuclear fusion and fission.

3) ROBOTICS, AI:
Automation of services, manufacturing, construction, mobility.

4) DIGITALIZATION:
Computer systems including software and hardware; OS and applications.

5) SOCIAL ENTREPRENEURSHIP:
Applying the success factors of profit driven companies to non profits.
